title: When does World Series start? Schedule, TV channel for NL champion vs. AL champion
text:
The National League Championship Series is over, and the American League Championship Series is almost over.
The New York Mets advanced to the World Series with an 8-3 win over the Chicago Cubs on Wednesday. The Kansas City Royals lead the Toronto Blue Jays, 3-2, in the ALCS.
Now, after all that excitement, let the waiting begin.
The World Series won't begin until Tuesday at the field of the AL champ.
All of the games will be televised by Fox.
Here's the schedule of the best-of-7 series (all times are TBA):
Tuesday: New York Mets at American League
Wednesday: New York Mets at American League
Oct. 30: American League at New York Mets
Oct. 31: American League at New York Mets
x-Nov. 1: American League at New York Mets
x-Nov. 3: New York Mets at American League
x-Nov. 4: New York Mets at American League
x-if necessary
